SIMPLE: gleek
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gleek
<hw>Gleek</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. fr. Icel.
<ets>leika</ets> to play, play a trick on, with the prefix
<ets>ge-</ets>; akin to AS. <ets>gel⟦amac⟧can</ets>, Sw. <ets>leka</ets>
to play, Dan. <ets>lege</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A jest or scoff; a trick or deception.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Where's the Bastard's braves, and Charles his <qex>gleeks</qex>
?</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[Cf. <er>Glicke</er>]</ety> <def>An enticing look or
glance.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A pretty <qex>gleek</qex> coming from Pallas' eye.</q>
<rj><qau>Beau. & Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gleek</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Gleek
<hw>Gleek</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To make sport; to gibe; to sneer;
to spend time idly.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gleek</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Gleek
<hw>Gleek</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>glic</ets>, G.
<ets>gl⟦uum⟧ck</ets>, fortune. See <er>Luck</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A game at cards, once popular, played by three
persons.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Pepys. Evelyn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Three of the same cards held in the same hand; --
hence, three of anything.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gleeman</ent>⟦br⟧
